	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Gratia et pax etc.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Ut res humane caduce sunt et mortales, factum est, ut praesidium carnale multorum debitum universe carnis solverit<note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1">Als formelhafte Redewendung seit dem Mittelalter belegt; s. etwa Gesta Innocentii III., MPL CCXIV, Sp. XXXIX u.a.</note>, <persName ref="person126">Contzenus</persName> scilicet<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2"><persName ref="person126">Peter Kunz</persName> war am 11. Februar gestorben; s. oben <ref target="file11887">Nr. 1841</ref>, Anm. 66.</note>.</s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Post hac non valde pertimescendi duo superstites Lutherane factionis;<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3"><persName ref="person213">Simon Sulzer</persName> und <persName ref="person78">Beat Gering</persName>; zu ihrer fragwürdigen Charakterisierung als Lutheraner s. Amy Nelson <hi>Burnett,</hi> The Myth of the Swiss Lutherans: Martin Bucer and the Eucharistic Controversy in <placeName ref="place121">Bern</placeName>, in: Zwa 32, 2005, 45-70.</note> nam incertum est, num illis adiiciendus sit tercius, imo nobis non minor spes est de veritatis pio patrono, quare et vestrum erit vestras admovere manus auxiliatrices, ut ecclesia nostra ab isto onere levetur.</s>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Quod si vero nullus adiungetur, nihilominus maiori et spe et fructu pugnabimus; nam <persName ref="person126">Contzeni</persName> importunitati concedendum erat plurimum, ne simul totum edificium destrueretur.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Adolescens hic<note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4">Unbekannt.</note>, qui has meas ad te perfert litteras, a nobis anno elapso est receptus sicque vixit, ut forsitan<note xml:id="fna" type="footnote" n="a"><hi>Am Wortende ein gestrichener Buchstabe.</hi></note> propediem ad munus diaconatus vocabitur.</s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tu moneto, ne aliam quam sinceram et piam doctrinam et claram professionem imitetur, quae<note xml:id="fnb" type="footnote" n="b"><hi>Vor</hi> quae <hi>gestrichenes</hi> quam eam.</note> vulgata hactenus in ecclesiis Helveticis.<pb type="edition" next="108"/></s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Saluta meo nomine fratres omnes.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="de" type="auto">Datum <placeName ref="place121">Berne</placeName>, 23. februarii 1544.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><persName ref="person176">Erasmus Ritter</persName> ex animo tuus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse auf der Rückseite:]</note>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Et pio et docto viro domino Henrichio Bullingero<note xml:id="fnc" type="footnote" n="c"><hi>Vor</hi> Bullingero <hi>gestrichenes</hi> Bl.</note>, ecclesie Tigurine antistiti, fratri charissimo.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
